HEADWORD: Cibol
<hw>Cib"ol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>ciboule</ets>,
LL. <ets>cepula</ets>, <ets>cepola</ets>, dim. of L. <ets>cepa</ets>,
<ets>caepa</ets>, <ets>caepe</ets>, an onion. Cf. <er>Chibbal</er>,
<er>Cives</er>.]</ety> <def>A perennial alliaceous plant (<spn>Allium
fistulosum</spn>), sometimes called <xex>Welsh onion</xex>. Its fistular
leaves are used in cookery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

